  ('C', 37, $wiki_seed_v1$Continuous 连续的$wiki_seed_v1$, $wiki_seed_v1$A pattern is called Continuous if two neighboring faces match along the edge. That is to say, two adjacent edge cubies and corner cubies have the same color on the first face if and only if they have the same color on the second face. Continuous patterns are good candidates for exceptionally beautiful patterns.$wiki_seed_v1$, 'seed'),
