  ('C', 41, $wiki_seed_v1$Corner Twists 转角$wiki_seed_v1$, $wiki_seed_v1$The pieces of speedcubes need to move easily. Because of this sometimes corners can twist in their place. This can occur with very rounded corners as well as cubes on very loose tensions. A puzzle cannot be solved when a single corner twists in its place. It must be corrected before the solve can be finished.$wiki_seed_v1$, 'seed'),
