  ('T', 29, $wiki_seed_v1$Tymon's Challenge$wiki_seed_v1$, $wiki_seed_v1$Tymons Challenge is a measure of the time it takes a cuber to complete three sub-6 3x3 solves, not necessarily consecutively. A successful attempt accounts for the acts of 1) scrambling, 2) inspecting, and 3) timing for every completed solve. Entering times is not necessary, but solves must be timed on a Stackmat. Furthermore, at no point during an attempt may the cuber pause the timer.$wiki_seed_v1$, 'seed'),
  ('T', 30, $wiki_seed_v1$The challenge was invented by Lucas Etter, who drew inspiration from Tymon Kolasinksis Fast Friday videos. Each Friday, Tymon would record three sub-6 3x3 solves, but Lucas saw the opportunity in adding a time component to Tymons plan. Hence, Tymons Challenge is simply the continuous version of recording three sub-6 3x3 solves. It sheds a new light on engaging practice.$wiki_seed_v1$, $wiki_seed_v1$$wiki_seed_v1$, 'seed'),
